# name: test_scaffold_output_snapshot
  '''
  Implement all `pytest.skip("implement me")` stubs in the test file: $ARGUMENTS
  
  ## How this project is structured
  
  - Router test files: tests/generated/test_{tag}.py
  - Service test stubs: tests/generated/test_{tag}_service.py
  - Service files: src/services/{tag}.py
  - Factory helpers for building response objects: tests/generated/conftest.py
  - Each test class maps to one API endpoint (documented in the class docstring)
  
  ## The service mock pattern
  
  Each test class has access to:
  - `client_with_mock` — a TestClient with the service dependency overridden
  - `mock_service` — an AsyncMock(spec={Tag}Service) wired into that client
  
  The service method name is the snake_case operationId from the router (matches the
  function name in generated/routers/{tag}/router.py).
  
  ## Error handling convention
  
  Not-found errors in this project:
    `HTTPException(status_code=404, detail='Not found')`
  
  Configure with: `mock_service.{method}.side_effect = HTTPException(status_code=404, detail='Not found')`
  
  ## Implementation steps
  
  1. Read $ARGUMENTS and list all methods containing `pytest.skip("implement me")`
  2. For each stub:
     a. Read the hint comments above the `pytest.skip` line — they show the exact
        mock setup, request call, and assertion to use
     b. If no hints are present, read the class docstring for the endpoint, then
        read tests/generated/conftest.py to find the right factory function
  3. Implement `test_success`:
     - Set `mock_service.{method}.return_value` to a factory-built instance
     - Call the endpoint via `client_with_mock`
     - Assert `response.status_code == 200` (201 for POST) and spot-check the JSON
  4. Implement `test_not_found`:
     - Set `mock_service.{method}.side_effect` to the not-found exception above
     - Call the endpoint via `client_with_mock`
     - Assert `response.status_code == 404`
  5. For POST/PUT/PATCH `test_success`: check the hint comment — if it flags
     "adjust return_value to match your service logic", implement a basic assertion
     (status code only) and leave a TODO comment for domain logic
  6. After all stubs are implemented, run:
     `uv run pytest $ARGUMENTS -v`
     Fix any failures before finishing.
  
  '''
# ---
